The President's New Clothes
Donald Trump has been president of the United States for less than 150 days, and to say his term has been less than remarkably historical would be a grave understatement. Given the historical context of the treatment of minorities in America, it is relatively odd to think the election of another white male would be more impactful than the election of its first African-American president but that is the silent question being asked in the minds of most Americans today. It is far too early to tell if the Trump administration will be a success unparalleled or if it will go down as the greatest miscarriage of trust by the United States government against its people. If Trump's first 100 or so days are an indicator of what else is to come, it appears that America has turned into a tale by Hans Christian Andersen....
-An excerpt from The President's New Clothes

Acting FBI Director Andrew McCabe disputed White House claims that rank and file members of the Federal Bureau of Investigations had "lost confidence" in former Director James Comey. McCabe was testifying before a Senate panel this morning. "Director Comey enjoyed broad support within the FBI and still does to this day," McCabe said in response to questions at a hearing before the Senate Intelligence Committee. "I can confidently tell you that the majority, the vast majority of FBI employees enjoyed a deep and positive connection to Director Comey." Read our full coverage on TIME.com.
